  "instructions": [
    "preheat the oven to 375f (190c).",
    "grease an 8-inch square baking dish with coconut oil and set aside.",
    "in a large mixing bowl, combine the oats, almond milk, cocoa powder, sugar, and melted coconut oil. Mix well until the oats are evenly coated.",
    "add the eggs, yogurt, and vanilla extract to the bowl and mix until the batter is smooth.",
    "stir in the unsweetened shredded coconut and caramelized chocolate chips.",
    "pour the batter into the prepared baking dish and smooth the top.",
    "bake for 35-40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.",
    "remove from the oven and let cool slightly before slicing and serving."
